  "body": "Hi all,\n\nI used isolated ribosome tomograms to run Warp-Relion-M subtomo average. \nThe pre-processing is proceseed by Warp. Relion refines a 7.4A map using \nabout 12,000 subtomograms. However, M produced a 50A map. I uncheck every \nbox and run 1 iteration using 100% particles to see if M will re-produce a \nsimilar map like Relion. However, M still produce a 50A map.\n\nI used Alister's scripts to down-version the star file from Relion3.1 and \ncheck the units of shift is right. The XX_fsc.star produced by M looks \nstrange because the correlation of 2 half maps is negative between 50A to \n20A. sometimes, the correlation is -1. I attach the XX_fsc.star below.\n\nIs there any clue to do the trouble-shooting? Really appreciate your advice.\n\nBest,\nJialu\n\n\n--------------------------------------------------------------------\n\ndata_\n\nloop_\n_wrpResolution #1\n_wrpFSCUnmasked #2\n_wrpFSCRandomized #3\n_wrpFSCCorrected #4\n_wrpFSCMasked #5\n  Infinity              1              1              1              1\n     601.6      0.9943152      0.9999955      0.9999962      0.9999962\n     300.8      0.9981717       0.999985      0.9999865      0.9999865\n  200.5333      0.9987051      0.9999562      0.9999584      0.9999584\n     150.4      0.9965022      0.9998554      0.9998587      0.9998587\n    120.32      0.9830461      0.9993832      0.9994031      0.9994031\n  100.2667      0.9691125      0.9985872      0.9986564      0.9986564\n  85.94286       0.960398       0.998244      0.9982107      0.9982107\n      75.2       0.923426      0.9971949      0.9967543      0.9967543\n  66.84445      0.8371596      0.9951468      0.9939438      0.9939438\n     60.16      0.7283027      0.9902782       0.988903       0.988903\n  54.69091      0.4963332      0.9808248       0.981636       0.981636\n  50.13334       0.308367      0.9760745     -0.1899881      0.9715289\n  46.27692      0.2324384      0.9709504     -0.5673173      0.9544701\n  42.97143     0.0